Search is still on for possible rescue or finding the remains of Motunrayo John who was swept away by flood in Ikare-Akoko. Motunrayo is a JSS Three student of Mount Carmel College. The incident happened on Tuesday at about 4.30pm after a heavy downpour that lasted four hours. Sources said the victim was being taken home by her father on a motorcycle when then incident occurred.   Bandits demand N150m to free Plateau monarch     Army intercepts carload of explosives in Cross River     Court orders Mompha’s arrest in N6b laundering suit   According to witness, “It was when her father was returning her home that the incident occurred on River Dada bridge “The velocity of the flood which had spilled on to the road made the bike to fall and in the process, both the victim and her father fell. “Unfortunately, the father was able to come out but the girl was swept away by the flood. “We are still searching for the girl.” Ondo Police spokesman, SP Fumilayo Odunlami, could not be reached for comments.